</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A European court yesterday reduced EC fines on some chemical companies
accused of operating a cartel in polypropylene, writes David Buchan in
Brussels.
The Court of First Instance reduced the fines on Shell from Ecu9m (Pounds
6.39m) to Ecu8.1m, on ICI from Ecu10m to 9m, and on Huls of Germany from
Ecu2.7m to 2.3m, because it said these companies were not part of the cartel
for as long as the Commission had claimed.
