FT  11 MAR 92 / International Capital Markets: Bank rules alter in
Philippines
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MANILA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Central Bank of the Philippines announced yesterday that the period
within which banks will be allowed to be in chronic reserve deficiency is to
be reduced to two from four consecutive weeks, effective from March 21,
AP-DJ reports from Manila.
The bank said this would improve the management of reserve and base money
programmes, particularly meeting targeted monetary aggregate levels.
It said the reserve position of a bank and the penalty on reserve deficiency
is to be based on a seven-day week and other days when there is no central
clearing.
