<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAR 92 / Sunday trade ruling reserved
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE House of Lords has reserved judgment on an appeal over the powers of
local authorities in England and Wales to enforce Sunday trading laws. The
decision is not expected before next month.
Kirklees Borough Council, West Yorkshire, backed by attorney general Sir
Patrick Mayhew, hopes to overturn a Court of Appeal ruling which made Sunday
trading restrictions virtually unenforceable.
A European Court ruling on the validity of Sunday trading laws in England
and Wales under European Community law is expected later this year.
The Kirklees appeal concerns whether local authorities, seeking court
injunctions banning Sunday trading, must indemnify retailers for loss of
Sunday profits in the event of the European Court upholding the traders'
position.
