FT  10 MAR 92 / International Company News: Joint venture bank set up in the
Ukraine
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN FRIEDMAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
AIOC, a New York-based commodity trader, has joined forces with four
Ukrainian state enterprises and with Bank Mees &amp; Hope, the merchant banking
division of ABN-Amro of the Netherlands, to form a joint venture bank in the
Ukraine.
The new bank, with initial capital of Dollars 20m, will be called First
Ukrainian International Bank and will be run by an executive of Bank Mees &amp;
Hope who will move from Amsterdam to Kiev.
AIOC is the largest single shareholder, with more than 25 per cent of the
bank, while Bank Mees &amp; Hope has less than 25 per cent. The remaining 50 per
cent of the bank is owned by Promstrojbank, the state-owned bank, plus three
Ukrainian state enterprises.
Mr Alan Clingman, president and majority shareholder of AIOC, said the idea
of forming a bank developed as he and other commodity traders found it
difficult to do business in the Ukraine without any local institutions that
had foreign exchange expertise.
