FT  10 MAR 92 / UK News (Employment): Woman manager fights demotion
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CATHERINE MILTON, Labour Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE MOST senior woman in the marketing department of British Gas lost her
job to a man junior to her and was praised for taking the news 'like a man',
an industrial tribunal in London heard yesterday.
Ms Hilary Williams, who earns Pounds 45,000 a year and was formerly regional
marketing services manager for the British Gas south-west region, was the
only manager of her grade demoted in a reorganisation over the past two
years. All 11 male managers kept their jobs. Ms Williams is claiming sex
discrimination.
The case hinges on whether Ms Williams' original job was significantly
changed by the reorganisation. Guidelines said managers would retain their
jobs where those jobs did not change substantially, irrespective of
performance.
British Gas said the post created by the reorganisation contained an
additional information technology element amounting to 30 per cent of the
workload. This meant the post could be advertised.
Ms Williams's lawyer Miss Sue Ashtiany said the job descriptions drawn up
for advertisements before and after the reorganisation were similar and that
Mr Peter Barham, who won the post, had no special information technology
qualifications.
Miss Ashtiany said Ms Williams contested British Gas's view that Mr Barham
had done her job better than she did while she was on secondment to British
Gas in London. She said that before the reorganisation senior managers had
judged Ms Williams as demonstrating good potential for further development.
Later, she was described as relying on instinct rather than hard facts.
Ms Williams was among British Gas's top 700 managers. She joined the
organisation in 1983 after holding jobs in the prison service, local
government, an oil company and a management consultancy.
The case continues today.
A female pool champion will today, at an industrial tribunal in Leeds,
accuse the Professional Pool Players Organisation of failing to grant her
professional status even though she has won many tournaments.
</TEXT>
